SIMPLE: painting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Painting
<hw>Paint"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or employment
of laying on, or adorning with, paints or colors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>The work of the painter;
also, any work of art in which objects are represented in color on a
flat surface; a colored representation of any object or scene; a
picture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Color laid on; paint.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A depicting by words; vivid representation in
words.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Picture</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paintless</ent>⟦br⟧
